          when you visit our site. A cookie is a small file of letters and numbers that we put on your computer. The cookies
          we use aid us in improving our site and your experience by tracking which areas and features of our site are popular,
          making the site easier to navigate, count visits, and allow a registered user to remain signed in to his/her user
          profile throughout a visit. We may also use cookies placed on our site by third parties acting on our behalf. If
          you want to opt out of our cookies, you can delete them and any other cookies that are already on your computer.
          Please refer to the help and support areas on your Internet browser for instructions on how to locate the file
          or directory that stores cookies. Some functionalities on our site may be affected if you delete our cookies.
        </p>
        <b>Online Donations</b>
        <p>
